# WebSocket Connection Tests for STR Agentic Adventures
# Use the REST Client extension in VS Code to test these endpoints

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@campaignId = test-campaign-123
@characterId = test-character-456

### Test 1: Check if backend is running
GET {{baseUrl}}/docs
Accept: text/html

### Test 2: Test basic API health (if available)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/
Accept: application/json

### Test 3: Test game API router availability
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/game/campaigns
Accept: application/json

### Test 4: Create a test character first
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/character
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Character",
  "race": "Human",
  "character_class": "Fighter", 
  "abilities": {
    "strength": 15,
    "dexterity": 14,
    "constitution": 13,
    "intelligence": 12,
    "wisdom": 10,
    "charisma": 8
  },
  "backstory": "A brave test character"
}

### Test 5: Create a test campaign
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/campaign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Campaign",
  "setting": "Fantasy Adventure",
  "world_description": "A magical world for testing",
  "tone": "heroic"
}

### Test 6: Test the REST API fallback endpoint that should work
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/input
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "I look around the room",
  "character_id": "{{characterId}}",
  "campaign_id": "{{campaignId}}"
}

### Test 7: Test dice rolling endpoint
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/dice/roll
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notation": "1d20"
}

### Test 8: Test WebSocket endpoint accessibility (this will fail in REST client but shows endpoint exists)
# Note: WebSocket connections can't be tested with REST client, but we can verify the endpoint exists
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/ws/chat/{{campaignId}}
Accept: application/json

### Test 9: Test campaign WebSocket endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/ws/{{campaignId}}
Accept: application/json

### Test 10: Test if the main app is configured correctly
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/game/character/{{characterId}}
Accept: application/json

### Test 11: Check OpenAPI docs for WebSocket routes
GET {{baseUrl}}/openapi.json
Accept: application/json

### Test 12: Test image generation (might fail due to Azure config)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/game/generate-image
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "image_type": "character_portrait",
  "details": {
    "name": "Test Character",
    "race": "Human",
    "class": "Fighter"
  }
}
